= render :partial => 'header'
%ul{:class => "nav nav-tabs"}
  = render :partial => 'tabs', :locals => { :level => 'compute'}

.container
  .row.quota-row
    .col-md-9   
      .row
        .col-md-2.quota-label
          .text-muted
            Instances
        .col-md-7
          .quota
            .quota-approved{:style => "right:40%"} 
              %span.text-nowrap
                Approved quota: 50 
            .quota-current
              %span.text-nowrap
                90
            .progress
              .progress-bar.progress-bar-quota{:style => "width:40%"} 40
              .progress-bar.progress-bar-empty{:style => "width:20%"}
              .progress-bar.progress-bar-quota.quota-overcommit{:style => "width:40%"}
        .col-md-1.quota-request-more
          = link_to 'Details', '#', class: 'btn btn-primary btn-sm', title: "open related service"
        .col-md-1.quota-request-more
          = link_to 'Request more',plugin('resource_management').resources_request_path(:level => 'compute', :resource_type => 'instances'), data: {modal: true}, class: 'btn btn-primary btn-sm'
    
      .row
        .col-md-2.quota-label
          .text-muted
            Ram (GiB)
        .col-md-7
          .quota
            .quota-current
              %span.text-nowrap
                100
            .progress
              .progress-bar.progress-bar-quota{:style => "width:80%"} 80
        .col-md-1.quota-request-more
          = link_to 'Details', '#', class: 'btn btn-primary btn-sm', title: "open related service"
        .col-md-1.quota-request-more
          = link_to 'Request more',plugin('resource_management').resources_request_path(:level => 'compute', :resource_type => 'ram'), data: {modal: true}, class: 'btn btn-primary btn-sm'
    
      = render :partial => 'bar', :locals => { :overview => false, :quota_data => { :approved => 20, :current => 20, :usage => 18 }, :percent => { :approved => 100, :usage => 90 }, :level => 'compute', :resource_type => 'cores', :name => 'Cores', :description => ''}
   
    .col-md-3
      .bs-callout.bs-callout-primary
        Good to know: I should like to see him try it; I'd give him such a pair of black eyes that he wouldn't dare to show his face in the admiral's cabin again for a long while, let alone down in the orlop there, where he lives, and hereabouts on the upper decks where he sneaks so much. Damn the devil, Flask; so you suppose I'm afraid of the devil? Who's afraid of him, except the old governor who daresn't catch him and put him in double-darbies, as he deserves, but lets him go about kidnapping people; aye, and signed a bond with him, that all the people the devil kidnapped, he'd roast for him? There's a governor!

    
